properties.headline: Gale Warning issued January 10 at 3:11AM CST until January 12 at 3:00AM CST by NWS Chicago IL
properties.description:
The National Weather Service in Chicago has issued a Gale
Warning, which is in effect from midnight tonight to 3 AM CST
Sunday. The Gale Watch is no longer in effect.

* WINDS...Northeast gales to 40 to 45 kt late tonight through
Saturday evening. A few higher gusts possible.

* SIGNIFICANT WAVES...To 18 ft late tonight through Saturday
evening.

* OCCASIONAL WAVES...To 23 ft late Friday night through Saturday
evening.
properties.instruction:
A Gale Warning means winds of 34 to 47 knots are imminent or
occurring. Operating a vessel in gale conditions requires
experience and properly equipped vessels. It is highly
recommended that mariners without the proper experience seek safe
harbor prior to the onset of gale conditions.

NWSheadline: GALE WARNING IN EFFECT FROM MIDNIGHT TONIGHT TO 3 AM CST SUNDAY
